-- Slovak State Railway Posts Loss on Interest-Rate Swaps, Sme Says
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-10-29T08:00:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-29/slovak-state-railway-posts-loss-on-interest-rate-swaps-sme-says.html
The state-owned Slovak Railway
Company lost more than 11 million euros ($14 million) in two
years until now on  interest-rate swaps ,  Sme  reported, citing
internal company documents.  Net present value of the derivative contracts, which the
company entered in 2006 and 2007 to hedge against rising
interest rates, is a 40 million euro loss, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  